

# 🌳 Level Order Traversal (Binary Tree)

---

## 📌 Concept

Traverse tree **level by level (BFS)** using a queue.

---

## ⚙️ Approach

* Use queue
* Add `root` and a `null` marker
* When `null` appears → level completed
* Store each level separately

---

## 💻 Code

```java
import java.util.*;

class Solution {
    public List<List<Integer>> levelOrder(TreeNode root) {
       
        Queue<TreeNode> q = new LinkedList<>();
        List<List<Integer>> mainList = new ArrayList<>();

        if(root == null)
        {
            return mainList;
        }

        q.add(root);
        q.add(null);

        List<Integer> list = new ArrayList<>();

        while(!q.isEmpty())
        {
            TreeNode data = q.remove();

            if(data == null)
            {
                mainList.add(list);
                list = new ArrayList<>();

                if(q.isEmpty())
                {
                    return mainList;
                }

                q.add(null);
            }
            else{
                list.add(data.val);

                if(data.left != null)
                {
                    q.add(data.left);
                }
                if(data.right != null)
                {
                    q.add(data.right);
                }
            }
        }
        return mainList;
    }
}
```

---

## 🔑 Key Points

* BFS traversal using queue
* `null` used to separate levels
* Each level stored as list

---

## ⏱️ Complexity

* Time: **O(n)**
* Space: **O(n)**

---

## 🧠 Learning

Level order = **queue + level separation pattern**
